<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900425-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>900425-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Petroleum Helicopters Inc.:   Industrial Equity (Pacific)   Files to Raise Stake to 25%</HL><DATE>04/25/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   PHEL H.IEP A.BRY</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Industrial Equity (Pacific) Ltd., a Hong Kong investmentfirm, said it filed with federal antitrust regulators toraise its stake in Petroleum Helicopters Inc. to as much as25%.   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, IndustrialEquity (Pacific) also said it sent a letter to PetroleumHelicopters Thursday saying it intended to seek boardrepresentation. According to the filing, that request wasdenied.</LP><TEXT>   In New Orleans, John La Plante, secretary and treasurer ofPetroleum Helicopters, had no comment &quot;at the present time,&quot;but he confirmed the company received the letter seekingrepresentation.   In December, Industrial Equity (Pacific) said it raisedits stake in Petroleum Helicopters to the equivalent of 17%,including an option to buy 12%.   In the filing, Industrial Equity (Pacific) said it haddiscussions with Petroleum Helicopters' management concerningways of maximizing long-term shareholder value and expects tocontinue such talks.   Petroleum Helicopters was quoted at $25.50 bid inover-the-counter trading.</TEXT></DOC>